reviews.text:
My family and I been coming to this Korean resturant for years.
We have tried different Korean restaurants  but this is the only one we return to.
The best for money value and a great selection of choices even for vegetarians.
Great decoration,Very polite/helpful waitresses and clean.
The best Korean restaurant in Wan Chai HK! So nice to dine here and with so reasonable price and professional chief!

Came to this place with my wife. We had a big spicy seafood hot pot that was filled with squid, crab, some shell fish and mix vegetables. Ordered a fried mackerel which is good too. Though price is a little on the high side, any order of a big dish do comes with 4 small dishes of kimchi and other seasoned vegetables. Do make reservation as there might be long que waiting sometime.

It's still awesome after all these years. I went 20+ years ago when it was back in Times Square. Now it's at W Square, but it's the same delicious foods. Do not wear your best sweater, jacket, or dress. They will smell like BBQ for 2 weeks. Staffs were wonderful. Ask for more Kim chee!
Excellent food nice setting great octopus and beef braised dish
